                                                                                                                         int zIndex)
        Parse all the ranges matching the given pattern in the given tree.
        The returned ranges will all have a dominance of NONE between them and the children of the given tree and will all have a dominance of NONE between another.
        The returned set is not guaranteed to be mutable nor immutable.
        Parameters:
        tree - the tree to parse in.
        pattern - the pattern to look for.
        zIndex - the z-index to accept.
        Returns:
        a set of references that matches the given pattern in the given tree.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given tree or pattern is null.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the reference of the given tree is out of the bounds of its document.
        java.io.IOError - if an I/O exception occurred while trying to read the document of the given tree.
        DocumentNotFoundError - if the document of the given tree is not available for reading.

      • parseAll

        @NotNull
 @Contract(value="_,_,_,_->new",
          pure=true)
public static @NotNull java.util.Set<java.util.List<Reference>> parseAll(@NotNull
                                                                                                                                           @NotNull Tree tree,
                                                                                                                                           @NotNull
                                                                                                                                           @NotNull java.util.regex.Pattern startPattern,
                                                                                                                                           @NotNull
                                                                                                                                           @NotNull java.util.regex.Pattern endPattern,
                                                                                                                                           int zIndex)
        Parse all the ranges starting with the given startPattern and ending with the given endPattern in the given tree.
        The returned set will be a set containing sets with each set having three references: one for the match, another for the starting sequence and a third for the ending sequence.
        The returned ranges will all have a dominance of Dominance.NONE between them and the children of the given tree and will have a dominance of NONE between each set of ranges.
        The returned set and its inner sets are not guaranteed to be mutable nor immutable.
        Parameters:
        tree - the tree to parse in.
        startPattern - the pattern matching the start of the ranges to look for.
        endPattern - the pattern matching the end of the ranges to look for.
        zIndex - the z-index to accept.
        Returns:
        a set of sets of ranges that matches the given pattern in the given tree.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given tree or startPattern or endPattern is null.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the reference of the given tree is out of the bounds of its document.
        java.io.IOError - if an I/O exception occurred while trying to read the document of the given tree.
        DocumentNotFoundError - if the document of the given tree is not available for reading.
        Since:
        0.2.0 ~2021.05.15

        Parse all the ranges starting with the given startPattern and ending with the given endPattern in the given tree.
        The returned set will be having three references: one for the match, another for the starting sequence and a third for the ending sequence.
        The returned ranges will all have a dominance of Dominance.NONE between them and the children of the given tree.
        The returned set and its inner sets are not guaranteed to be mutable nor immutable.
        Parameters:
        tree - the tree to parse in.
        startPattern - the pattern matching the start of the range to look for.
        endPattern - the pattern matching the end of the range to look for.
        zIndex - the z-index to accept.
        Returns:
        a set of the references matching the given pattern in the given tree.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given tree or startPattern or endPattern is null.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the reference of the given tree is out of the bounds of its document.
        java.io.IOError - if an I/O exception occurred while trying to read the document of the given tree.
        DocumentNotFoundError - if the document of the given tree is not available for reading.
